ost commonly used agents are beta-emitters, trontium 89 and amarium 153, and alpha-emitter, adium 223. hese agents have been shown to palliate pain due to bone metastasis.[56] s these agents also irradiate the bone marrow, myelosuppresion is the most prominent toxicity of these agents.
